@node "changes" "Changes"
@toc "main"

Changes to v1.1 (01/12/97)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
* Improved CPU Transcription code.  Gained up to 200% more speed in
  many cases.  Windows is now much faster!

* Fixed problem with selecting a display type in the CONFIGURE MODES
  sub-menu of the VIDEO menu.

* Added ability to create a CrossDOS compatible DOSDriver for any PCx
  partition or hardfile.  This allows reading/writing of PCx partitions
  and hardfiles from the Amiga side.  WARNING!!!! DO NOT MOUNT A PCx
  PARTITION OR HARDFILE *BEFORE* USING PCx OR CROSSDOS WILL CORRUPT THE
  DATA!!  The problem is that neither side is aware of each other and
  the FAT table and directory entries are cached on both sides, so
  changes will not be reflected properly, which almost always results
  in corrupted data.  You can DISMOUNT the DOSDriver and then use PCx.

  To create a DOSDriver, go to the DEVICES menu, select a device in
  LEFT window, and when it appears in the RIGHT window, select it
  and information about the driver, along with the ability to create
  a DOSDriver will be available.

  The default DOSDriver creation path is SYS:Storage/DOSDrivers/.
  You will need to locate this driver via Workbench, and double-click
  on it to activate it.  NOTE: DOSDrivers made for PCx partitions
  (not hardfiles), may need to be renamed to NOT match the original
  Amiga partition name. ie. DH2: could be PC_DH2:.

* Created new mshf.device to allow for CrossDOS mounted hardfiles.

* Corrected 'problem' with turning on data burst with processors using
  mix-n-match page and static column ram (A3000 machines).  It was
  possible for a machine with improperly matched memory types to crash
  when starting up the emulation's interface.

* New multi-os.device designed to handle the new extended sector/track
  format.

* New TURBO level setup.  Instead of the cycle gadget, a slider bar
  is now used.  You can change the Turbo Level from 1 to 7 (or OFF).
  Setting the Turbo Level to 4 will make Windows about 30% faster.
  Setting the Turbo Level to higher values will cause some things to
  speed up, and other things to slow down drastically.

* Corrected problem with systems that do not have continguous floppy
  drive units (ie. DF0 & DF2).

* Disabled drive B: until drive A: has been selected.

**************************************************************************

Changes to v1.0 (12/12/96)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------
Initial release

@endnode

@node "release" "1.1 Release Notes"
@toc "main"

                 * * *  L I M I T A T I O N S * * *
                 ----------------------------------

This emulation will not currently run Windows in enhanced mode or
Windows95.  Due to the poor performance in the past (we wrote e586DX)
with MMU emulation, we never intended to even support this.  We
have discovered a technique that will allow very fast support for
MMU paging, and we are currently working on this upgrade.

All standard upgrades and bug fixes will be made available free
of charge through Blittersoft's WEB page:

http://blittersoft.wildnet.co.uk

Click on the 'Microcode Solutions' logo to get upgrades and news.

Due to disk space restrictions the VGA_Graffiti video driver is
not included.  You can obtain this driver from Blittersoft's web
page.

PCxAFS does not currently have the read/write operations in place.
Due to a few problems reading/writing files, this feature (the primary
reason for the program's creation) has been temporarily disabled.  You
will be able to still mount an Amiga partition as a PC drive and
look at directorys and such, but you will not be able to copy files.
We are looking into these problems, and an upgraded PCxAFS program will
be made available through Blittersoft's WEB page as soon as it is
available.


If your Amiga does not have an FPU, then you MUST use the 'PCsx' version.
If the emulation crashes or does not start, try using this version
as you could have a faulty FPU.  PCx uses *every* FPU command that is
available.

@endnode


